00:21:35,828 --> 00:21:39,574
If we don't make it that
far, I'm blaming you.

244
00:21:39,598 --> 00:21:41,743
I don't want to go by the
Wilkins' house anyway.

245
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:44,112
What? Are you still
thinking about those kids?

246
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:47,048
Bill, they were huge, and they
chased us for, like, an hour.

247
00:21:47,072 --> 00:21:49,084
Don't be a baby.

248
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:53,588
You were just as scared as me. We
were lost and we were both crying.

249
00:21:53,612 --> 00:21:55,590
Yeah, but they
really got to you.

250
00:21:55,614 --> 00:21:59,083
- They were really scary.
- Yeah.

251
00:22:01,754 --> 00:22:04,566
Anyway, she better
not slow us down.

252
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:08,403
Maggie's cool, you'll see. Anyway,
if anyone slows us down, it's you.

253
00:22:08,427 --> 00:22:12,574
- You run like a grandma.
- Nuh-uh. A race car grandma, maybe.

254
00:22:12,598 --> 00:22:15,543
- That doesn't even make sense.
- You don't make sense.

255
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:18,369
Gotta go. Bye, weirdo.

256
00:23:04,716 --> 00:23:07,429
Hey!

257
00:23:07,453 --> 00:23:08,663
Where were you?

258
00:23:08,687 --> 00:23:10,565
Jumpy much?

259
00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:12,734
I didn't see you.

260
00:23:12,758 --> 00:23:15,103
I thought maybe you didn't come.

261
00:23:15,127 --> 00:23:17,672
Nah, don't worry.

262
00:23:17,696 --> 00:23:19,941
I'm always here.

263
00:23:19,965 --> 00:23:22,644
You scared me.

264
00:23:22,668 --> 00:23:24,479
I can't help it if you're blind.

265
00:23:24,503 --> 00:23:27,505
I've just been right
here the whole time.

266
00:24:55,727 --> 00:24:58,206
So what are you going as?
- For what?

267
00:24:58,230 --> 00:25:00,975
- Halloween, duh.
- I don't know.

268
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:02,911
Oh, come on. You have
to have some idea.

269
00:25:02,935 --> 00:25:08,216
Well, I remember for
the last Halloween,

270
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:11,252
- I went as a werewolf Princess.
- What?

271
00:25:11,276 --> 00:25:12,987
You heard me.

272
00:25:13,011 --> 00:25:15,557
What does that look like?

273
00:25:15,581 --> 00:25:19,060
Well... whoa. I had
the best fangs.

274
00:25:19,084 --> 00:25:23,097
And my mom had this fake
bearskin rug that I cut up.

275
00:25:23,121 --> 00:25:26,935
She was so mad. I had a
crown and a dress, too.

276
00:25:26,959 --> 00:25:28,870
I was beautiful.

277
00:25:28,894 --> 00:25:31,573
Sounds lovely.

278
00:25:31,597 --> 00:25:34,242
Well, I bet it's better than
whatever lame thing you're gonna be.

279
00:25:34,266 --> 00:25:37,011
Oh, just you wait.
I love Halloween.

280
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:38,680
- It's...
- It's the best.

281
00:25:38,704 --> 00:25:40,704
Yeah.

282
00:25:44,009 --> 00:25:47,922
- Do you ever think about it?
- -Think about what?

283
00:25:47,946 --> 00:25:52,727
Being a kid. Like, one
day you're not anymore.

284
00:25:52,751 --> 00:25:54,796
I guess.

285
00:25:54,820 --> 00:25:58,232
It feels like we've
been kids forever.

286
00:25:58,256 --> 00:26:01,970
- Yeah.
- But one day, you're not anymore.

287
00:26:01,994 --> 00:26:04,906
And it's not that long, really.

288
00:26:04,930 --> 00:26:06,931
That's really weird.

289
00:26:09,334 --> 00:26:11,379
Do you want to grow up?

290
00:26:11,403 --> 00:26:15,116
- Sometimes.
- I guess.

291
00:26:15,140 --> 00:26:18,208
But I like this so much.

292
00:26:34,926 --> 00:26:36,627
Come on, let's go across.

293
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:45,547
- Come on, it's not even that

294
00:26:45,559 --> 00:26:47,782
deep over here. - I can't.

295
00:26:47,806 --> 00:26:51,019
- Don't be a...
- I can't!

296
00:26:51,043 --> 00:26:54,612
- Why?
- I just can't, okay?

297
00:26:55,414 --> 00:26:57,114
Okay.

298
00:26:59,451 --> 00:27:02,697
Besides, there's a monster
on the other side.

299
00:27:02,721 --> 00:27:04,966
What? No, there's not.

300
00:27:04,990 --> 00:27:07,869
Yeah there is. I heard it.
It's true.

301
00:27:07,893 --> 00:27:11,873
It's a ghost, not a monster anyway, duh.
I heard it in school.

302
00:27:11,897 --> 00:27:15,076
They told it wrong then.
It's definitely a monster.

303
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:18,146
- You're making it up.
- No, I'm not. I swear.

304
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:20,948
I heard that there's a monster that
lives really deep in the woods

305
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:22,784
on the other side of the creek.

306
00:27:22,808 --> 00:27:25,853
It's really old and it waits
for kids to come out at night.

307
00:27:25,877 --> 00:27:29,279
- That's stupid. There's no...
- I don't want to go across.

308
00:27:31,049 --> 00:27:32,750
Okay.

309
00:27:49,968 --> 00:27:53,347
I had this weird
dream last night.

310
00:27:53,371 --> 00:27:55,850
What was it?

311
00:27:55,874 --> 00:27:58,252
A little bit like some of
the other dreams that I had

312
00:27:58,276 --> 00:28:01,389
after my mom and dad...

313
00:28:01,413 --> 00:28:04,392
You don't have to talk about
it if you don't want.

314
00:28:04,416 --> 00:28:08,496
It's okay. This one was
different from the others.

315
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:10,198
Why?

316
00:28:10,222 --> 00:28:13,034
I was in the woods,
but not this part.

317
00:28:13,058 --> 00:28:15,403
Somewhere else.

318
00:28:15,427 --> 00:28:20,775
It was creepy. I heard this...
voice.

319
00:28:20,799 --> 00:28:22,844
Do you remember what
the voice said?

320
00:28:22,868 --> 00:28:24,968
Yeah. It said my name.

321
00:28:27,439 --> 00:28:29,317
Don't go across
the creek, Peter.

322
00:28:29,341 --> 00:28:32,920
- Why?
- Just don't, okay? Promise.

323
00:28:32,944 --> 00:28:36,780
Okay, okay, I promise. Why
are you so weird about this?

324
00:28:38,350 --> 00:28:42,753
Some things don't go away
when you stop pretending.

325
00:30:43,141 --> 00:30:44,208
My pumpkin.

326
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:57,899
- Mom, mom, I have to tell you.
- Hi, honey, not now.

327
00:30:57,923 --> 00:30:59,600
But, mom, the
neighbors are gone.

328
00:30:59,624 --> 00:31:01,469
Well, maybe they
went out somewhere.

329
00:31:01,493 --> 00:31:03,905
- All of them?
- Honey, do I know?

330
00:31:03,929 --> 00:31:05,439
- I... - look, can you
tell me about this later?

331
00:31:05,463 --> 00:31:07,341
I have a million things
to do right now.

332
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:09,677
I realized the heat
was due this month,

333
00:31:09,701 --> 00:31:11,329
- and somehow I've got
to figure out how

334
00:31:11,341 --> 00:31:12,980
we're gonna... - there's
something wrong.

335
00:31:13,004 --> 00:31:14,916
You bet there's something wrong.

336
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:17,285
It takes a lot to keep this
little ship afloat, bub.

337
00:31:17,309 --> 00:31:20,221
- But...
- I said not now!

338
00:31:20,245 --> 00:31:25,192
There's food and dinner and
stuff on their tables.

339
00:31:25,216 --> 00:31:27,094
Well, maybe they went
out for something.

340
00:31:27,118 --> 00:31:29,130
How do you know there's
food on the table?

341
00:31:29,154 --> 00:31:30,398
Were you looking in their house?

342
00:31:30,422 --> 00:31:32,500
- But...
- Were you?

343
00:31:32,524 --> 00:31:35,503
- Just listen for a second.
- Why would you do something like this?

344
00:31:35,527 --> 00:31:38,272
We just moved here. We're
trying to settle in.

345
00:31:38,296 --> 00:31:39,540
We're trying to
make a new start,

346
00:31:39,564 --> 00:31:41,208
and you're spying
on the neighbors?

347
00:31:41,232 --> 00:31:42,944
Peter, you know how
hard this has been.

348
00:31:42,968 --> 00:31:44,445
Why would you try
and make it harder?

349
00:31:44,469 --> 00:31:46,080
I'm not trying to
make it harder.

350
00:31:46,104 --> 00:31:49,550
Would you please listen
and stop being so stupid?

351
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:52,186
That's it, up to bed.

352
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:55,256
Now.

353
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:56,980
Vamonos.

354
00:33:56,534 --> 00:33:59,469
Hey, Peter. Come in here.

355
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:43,858
Peter! Peter!

356
00:34:43,882 --> 00:34:48,295
Peter? Peter? What's wrong?

357
00:34:48,319 --> 00:34:50,798
Oh, oh. It was just a dream.

358
00:34:50,822 --> 00:34:55,703
It was just a dream, okay?
Are you okay?

359
00:34:55,727 --> 00:34:57,727
I heard you again.

360
00:35:01,199 --> 00:35:03,878
I'm sorry I got so
angry earlier, babe.

361
00:35:03,902 --> 00:35:08,182
Oh, no, no, no, no. Please, don't cry.
Don't cry.

362
00:35:08,206 --> 00:35:11,352
It's okay. God. Oh,
it's a mess, isn't it?

363
00:35:11,376 --> 00:35:13,554
I'm a mess, and...
And you're a mess.

364
00:35:13,578 --> 00:35:18,448
But... but we're okay, right?
The two of us, we're okay.

365
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:55,462
I'm telling you,
something is wrong.

366
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:57,498
You were dreaming. You
always sleepwalk.

367
00:35:57,522 --> 00:35:59,366
You really freaked me out the
first time you stayed over.

368
00:35:59,390 --> 00:36:02,870
I swear I wasn't sleeping.

369
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:05,472
Ah, so you're trying to tell me

370
00:36:05,496 --> 00:36:07,374
that the basement talked to you

371
00:36:07,398 --> 00:36:10,311
and then a monster tried
to break in your house.

372
00:36:10,335 --> 00:36:11,679
Well, yeah.

373
00:36:11,703 --> 00:36:15,549
Did your mom see the monster?

374
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:18,719
The monster was gone
before my mom got there.

375
00:36:18,743 --> 00:36:20,521
Ah-ha.

376
00:36:20,545 --> 00:36:22,356
Well, what about all
the missing people?

377
00:36:22,380 --> 00:36:24,558
- What missing people?
- My neighbors.

378
00:36:24,582 --> 00:36:26,760
Your neighbors aren't missing.

379
00:36:26,784 --> 00:36:28,629
Well, something's going on.

380
00:36:28,653 --> 00:36:32,399
You're right. You've got
a crazy imagination.

381
00:36:32,423 --> 00:36:36,403
Remember the time when you tried to make
me believe that my toys came to life

382
00:36:36,427 --> 00:36:39,740
and you only ended up scaring yourself
and locking all your toys in the closet?

383
00:36:39,764 --> 00:36:42,409
This is totally different.
I'm not making this up.

384
00:36:42,433 --> 00:36:44,578
Maggie said there was something
weird about this place.

385
00:36:44,602 --> 00:36:47,481
There is something weird
about this place... you.

386
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:51,318
Maggie said there was a monster or
something that lived in the woods.

387
00:36:51,342 --> 00:36:52,620
Not a ghost, by the way.

388
00:36:52,644 --> 00:36:54,588
That's not what I heard.

389
00:36:54,612 --> 00:36:56,957
Well, Maggie knows
more than you.

390
00:36:56,981 --> 00:36:59,360
And you are scared of
your toys coming to life.

391
00:36:59,384 --> 00:37:02,429
- Hey!
- Well, the point is

392
00:37:02,453 --> 00:37:06,367
that I used to believe
that, well...

393
00:37:06,391 --> 00:37:08,736
Well, you shouldn't believe,
'cause it's not real.

394
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:14,531
There's no such thing as monsters,
ghosts, bigfoots, or any of that stuff.

395
00:37:16,401 --> 00:37:18,746
There might be aliens.
We just don't know.

396
00:37:18,770 --> 00:37:21,615
- Bill, I'm trying to tell you...
- Okay, um, sorry. I gotta go.

397
00:37:21,639 --> 00:37:25,753
Uh, you go home and get some rest or...
Something.

398
00:37:25,777 --> 00:37:27,921
Uh, see you tomorrow.

399
00:37:27,945 --> 00:37:30,491
Well, just remember
to be careful.

400
00:37:30,515 --> 00:37:34,028
You do you know that this is how
my crazy uncle Bruce sounded

401
00:37:34,052 --> 00:37:35,696
before they took
him to the home,

402
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:39,856
but my mom pretended
he moved to Florida?

403
00:38:31,075 --> 00:38:33,076
Peter.

404
00:40:16,781 --> 00:40:19,760
Peter!

405
00:40:19,784 --> 00:40:22,763
Maggie? What's going on?

406
00:40:22,787 --> 00:40:24,865
- We've got to go.
- What? Where am I?

407
00:40:24,889 --> 00:40:28,724
Come on, you're in danger.
We've got to go!

408
00:40:31,629 --> 00:40:35,064
It's here.

409
00:43:38,082 --> 00:43:41,395
It's okay. I don't
hear anything.

410
00:43:41,419 --> 00:43:43,397
I think we're safe now.

411
00:43:43,421 --> 00:43:45,432
Come on, we can head
back to my house.

412
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:47,968
Back that way?

413
00:43:47,992 --> 00:43:50,904
No. We can cross the
creek and follow it

414
00:43:50,928 --> 00:43:53,306
on the other side to the road.

415
00:43:53,330 --> 00:43:54,964
Come on.

416
00:44:06,343 --> 00:44:09,746
What's wrong, really?

417
00:44:14,318 --> 00:44:16,430
I lied before.

418
00:44:16,454 --> 00:44:19,399
What?

419
00:44:19,423 --> 00:44:21,401
There is a ghost.

420
00:44:21,425 --> 00:44:24,204
What do you mean?

421
00:44:24,228 --> 00:44:26,229
She died here.

422
00:44:28,365 --> 00:44:30,277
No.

423
00:44:30,301 --> 00:44:32,045
No, you're a kid.

424
00:44:32,069 --> 00:44:33,880
I used to be.

425
00:44:33,904 --> 00:44:37,350
- Stop lying!
- I'm not lying. I'm not.

426
00:44:37,374 --> 00:44:39,052
You have to be because
that's crazy.

427
00:44:39,076 --> 00:44:41,888
Why do you think no one
has ever seen me before?

428
00:44:41,912 --> 00:44:44,291
Why do you think
I'm always here?

429
00:44:44,315 --> 00:44:45,782
No.

430
00:44:47,118 --> 00:44:50,119
No. I don't believe you.

431
00:44:53,424 --> 00:44:54,968
Look at me.

432
00:44:54,992 --> 00:44:56,325
Really look.

433
00:44:58,763 --> 00:45:00,430
Believing is seeing.

434
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:49,189
How can you be dead?

435
00:45:49,213 --> 00:45:52,259
Because no one came to help,

436
00:45:52,283 --> 00:45:54,828
and the water was too strong.

437
00:45:54,852 --> 00:45:56,519
And I couldn't keep it out.

438
00:46:02,159 --> 00:46:04,460
Please don't be afraid of me.

439
00:46:09,233 --> 00:46:11,400
So that's why you can't cross.

440
00:46:19,510 --> 00:46:23,890
We can stay on this side if we
cut through the playground.

441
00:46:23,914 --> 00:46:25,414
Come on.

442
00:46:30,554 --> 00:46:33,600
What's it like?

443
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:37,827
It's... lonely.

444
00:46:51,342 --> 00:46:54,588
After they found me,

445
00:46:54,612 --> 00:46:58,181
my mom came to the creek
one time to visit.

446
00:47:11,061 --> 00:47:13,062
She was crying.

447
00:47:18,936 --> 00:47:21,181
I wanted to tell her
I was right here,

448
00:47:21,205 --> 00:47:22,949
but I couldn't.

449
00:47:22,973 --> 00:47:25,074
Grownups can't see.

450
00:47:28,012 --> 00:47:32,025
Later, my mom and
dad moved away,

451
00:47:32,049 --> 00:47:33,950
but I couldn't go with them.

452
00:48:01,111 --> 00:48:02,522
When I was little,

453
00:48:02,546 --> 00:48:06,983
my dad made up these
great bedtime stories.

454
00:48:08,452 --> 00:48:13,199
He used all these great voices.

455
00:48:13,223 --> 00:48:16,425
But I didn't know
dads could be liars.

456
00:48:19,296 --> 00:48:23,476
I don't know what
I'd do if he died.

457
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:26,002
You must miss them a lot.

458
00:48:29,239 --> 00:48:31,384
I'm sorry I didn't tell you.

459
00:48:31,408 --> 00:48:34,154
I thought maybe...

460
00:48:34,178 --> 00:48:35,422
You'd leave me.

461
00:48:35,446 --> 00:48:38,058
Never. We're best friends.

462
00:48:38,082 --> 00:48:39,582
Right?

463
00:48:45,656 --> 00:48:48,702
Do you like to know
how it happened?

464
00:48:48,726 --> 00:48:50,927
It's a scary story.

465
00:48:53,564 --> 00:48:55,742
There really is a monster.

466
00:48:55,766 --> 00:49:00,046
My sister told me to scare
me, but she was right.

467
00:49:00,070 --> 00:49:01,614
I saw it.

468
00:49:01,638 --> 00:49:04,184
It takes kids away.

469
00:49:04,208 --> 00:49:08,722
It tried to get me, but there
was a storm, and I got lost.

470
00:49:08,746 --> 00:49:11,691
It wants you next.
It's calling you.

471
00:49:11,715 --> 00:49:15,195
And I don't think it's gonna
stop until it gets you.

472
00:49:15,219 --> 00:49:17,430
Why me?

473
00:49:17,454 --> 00:49:19,733
Because you're the kid
who finally came.

474
00:49:19,757 --> 00:49:23,370
Haven't you noticed there aren't
any other kids around here?

475
00:49:23,394 --> 00:49:25,138
Yeah, I guess.

476
00:49:25,162 --> 00:49:27,707
Bill said the last time
kids lived around here

477
00:49:27,731 --> 00:49:30,410
was when his mom was little.

478
00:49:30,434 --> 00:49:33,213
People don't know
the real reason,

479
00:49:33,237 --> 00:49:36,205
but they learn. This
is not a good place.

480
00:49:38,609 --> 00:49:41,254
Maybe that's why all the
grownups are leaving.

481
00:49:41,278 --> 00:49:44,624
That's what grownups
do sometimes.

482
00:49:44,648 --> 00:49:46,393
I think this is different.

483
00:49:46,417 --> 00:49:49,763
I think the monster
is taking them away.

484
00:49:49,787 --> 00:49:52,432
We've got to do something.

485
00:49:52,456 --> 00:49:55,368
What?

486
00:49:55,392 --> 00:49:57,737
My mom and I are used to moving.

487
00:49:57,761 --> 00:50:00,407
You can come with.

488
00:50:00,431 --> 00:50:03,243
Your mom won't believe you.
You know she won't.

489
00:50:03,267 --> 00:50:06,546
And... I can't leave.

490
00:50:06,570 --> 00:50:10,083
Oh, I'm sorry.

491
00:50:10,107 --> 00:50:12,118
What are we supposed to do then?

492
00:50:12,142 --> 00:50:14,754
I don't know.

493
00:50:14,778 --> 00:50:16,779
- Peter?
- Bill?

494
00:50:20,851 --> 00:50:22,829
What are you doing here?

495
00:50:22,853 --> 00:50:25,498
Oh, you know, just going for a
run in the middle of the night

496
00:50:25,522 --> 00:50:27,400
because my toys are
trying to kill me.

497
00:50:27,424 --> 00:50:30,370
- What?
- All right, you win.

498
00:50:30,394 --> 00:50:32,772
I just had to crawl out
of my bathroom window

499
00:50:32,796 --> 00:50:34,741
because a doll was trying
to break down the door.

500
00:50:34,765 --> 00:50:38,144
All right, calm down. Calm
down, you're safe now.

501
00:50:38,168 --> 00:50:40,447
Safe? Somehow, I don't think so.

502
00:50:40,471 --> 00:50:42,449
Anyway, what are you doing here?

503
00:50:42,473 --> 00:50:46,086
Escaping from the monster.
That's real, too, by the way.

504
00:50:46,110 --> 00:50:48,611
Great. "Calm down," he says.

505
00:50:50,147 --> 00:50:52,792
- Ahem.
- Uh, bill, this is Maggie.

506
00:50:52,816 --> 00:50:55,295
Hi, Maggie, I'm bill. Not Billy.

507
00:50:55,319 --> 00:50:57,330
Hi. Why not Billy?

508
00:50:57,354 --> 00:51:00,533
'Cause then the people take me
more seriously if I'm bill.

509
00:51:00,557 --> 00:51:02,669
There are plenty of bills
that people respect.

510
00:51:02,693 --> 00:51:06,372
Bill Clinton, bill
nye, the science guy.

511
00:51:06,396 --> 00:51:08,274
- Does it work?
- Not really.

512
00:51:08,298 --> 00:51:09,776
My mom just calls
me the unpaid bill.

513
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:11,644
Look, I hate to be rude,

514
00:51:11,668 --> 00:51:13,546
but what the heck are we
supposed to do about this?

515
00:51:13,570 --> 00:51:16,705
Would you be quite for a second?
I'm trying to think.

516
00:51:21,645 --> 00:51:25,391
This would all go away if the
monster goes away, right?

517
00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:28,595
- How does she know?
- She just knows, okay?

518
00:51:28,619 --> 00:51:30,619
But that's right, right?

519
00:51:35,692 --> 00:51:37,670
We've gotta fight it, don't we?

520
00:51:37,694 --> 00:51:39,572
What? Are you crazy?

521
00:51:39,596 --> 00:51:41,508
Maybe.

522
00:51:41,532 --> 00:51:43,243
But I think we have to.

523
00:51:43,267 --> 00:51:45,178
We're a bunch of stupid kids.

524
00:51:45,202 --> 00:51:47,747
Bill, it's after me, and
it's not gonna stop.

525
00:51:47,771 --> 00:51:49,782
None of us are safe now.

526
00:51:49,806 --> 00:51:51,751
What?

527
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:53,720
It tried to get you, too.

528
00:51:53,744 --> 00:51:55,355
Did you try and get him to help?

529
00:51:55,379 --> 00:51:57,490
- Yeah.
- That's why.

530
00:51:57,514 --> 00:51:59,192
It doesn't want
you to have help,

531
00:51:59,216 --> 00:52:00,627
and it's just going
to get worse.

532
00:52:00,651 --> 00:52:03,730
- Great.
- She's right. You're right.

533
00:52:03,754 --> 00:52:07,800
Grownups won't ever believe
until it's too late.

534
00:52:07,824 --> 00:52:11,571
It's up to us. Are you
going to help or not?

535
00:52:11,595 --> 00:52:16,476
Fine. But if I die, I'm
going to be so mad at you.

536
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:18,378
Okay, tomorrow
night's Halloween.

537
00:52:18,402 --> 00:52:20,313
That's when we'll do it.

538
00:52:20,337 --> 00:52:22,482
Our parents will think we're
going out trick or treating,

539
00:52:22,506 --> 00:52:23,783
so wear your costume.

540
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:26,586
We'll meet at my house. Come on.

541
00:52:26,610 --> 00:52:28,288
This was all gonna be so good.

542
00:52:28,312 --> 00:52:33,626
Get a ton of candy, scare
the pants off of Peter...

543
00:52:33,650 --> 00:52:36,496
I hate to tell you this,
but if we fight it,

544
00:52:36,520 --> 00:52:39,666
I think it will know,
and it will be angry.

545
00:52:39,690 --> 00:52:43,225
I picked the wrong people to
trick or treat with this year.

546
00:53:07,017 --> 00:53:09,919
Do you... sleep?

547
00:53:12,656 --> 00:53:15,468
Don't worry about it.

548
00:53:15,492 --> 00:53:17,493
I'll see you tomorrow.

549
00:53:44,021 --> 00:53:47,033
So the monster might
still be out there,

550
00:53:47,057 --> 00:53:50,036
because Victor Frankenstein
never finds him.

551
00:53:50,060 --> 00:53:53,006
But he wasn't really
a monster, was he?

552
00:53:53,030 --> 00:53:55,608
He had turned into a monster

553
00:53:55,632 --> 00:53:59,312
from loss and fear

554
00:53:59,336 --> 00:54:03,383
and loneliness and anger.

555
00:54:03,407 --> 00:54:05,385
That's the sad part.

556
00:54:05,409 --> 00:54:08,321
Had someone actually
taken the time

557
00:54:08,345 --> 00:54:10,990
to get to know the
person inside,

558
00:54:11,014 --> 00:54:12,774
maybe things would have
turned out different.

559
00:54:14,318 --> 00:54:16,329
Okay, class, that's
it for today.

560
00:54:16,353 --> 00:54:18,398
Remember your math
homework for tomorrow.

561
00:54:18,422 --> 00:54:20,500
And, hey, I know
tonight's Halloween,

562
00:54:20,524 --> 00:54:22,735
I know we're all
excited, but remember,

563
00:54:22,759 --> 00:54:24,760
be safe out there.

564
00:54:33,470 --> 00:54:36,616
- Are you ready for this?
- No.

565
00:54:36,640 --> 00:54:39,319
- Are you?
- No.

566
00:54:39,343 --> 00:54:41,954
We've gotta do something.

567
00:54:41,978 --> 00:54:44,857
Just look around.

568
00:54:44,881 --> 00:54:49,362
This is Halloween. There
should be people everywhere.

569
00:54:49,386 --> 00:54:50,763
This has gotta stop

570
00:54:50,787 --> 00:54:52,955
before everybody's gone.

571
00:54:56,059 --> 00:54:58,805
Remember, meet at
my house at eight.

572
00:54:58,829 --> 00:55:00,707
And bring your costume.

573
00:55:00,731 --> 00:55:03,843
Don't tell anyone.

574
00:55:03,867 --> 00:55:07,080
Even if they did believe us,
they'd just try and stop us.

575
00:55:07,104 --> 00:55:09,716
Maybe that's not
such a bad thing.

576
00:55:09,740 --> 00:55:11,751
Promise?

577
00:55:11,775 --> 00:55:13,776
All right, all right.

578
00:55:17,981 --> 00:55:20,860
See you later.

579
00:55:20,884 --> 00:55:22,885
Here goes nothing.

580
00:57:13,263 --> 00:57:15,875
Mom, what time is it?

581
00:57:15,899 --> 00:57:19,145
It's a quarter till eight. Are you excited?
It's finally here.

582
00:57:19,169 --> 00:57:21,881
- Yeah.
- Well, you could have fooled me.

583
00:57:21,905 --> 00:57:24,884
- No, I am.
- Honey, what's wrong?

584
00:57:24,908 --> 00:57:29,489
- Nothing.
- That's an awful big nothing.

585
00:57:29,513 --> 00:57:32,258
It's just this year...

586
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:34,026
Don't open the door.

587
00:57:34,050 --> 00:57:37,196
- Huh?
- Just leave the bowl of candy outside.

588
00:57:37,220 --> 00:57:38,965
Well, I thought you
said that was lame.

589
00:57:38,989 --> 00:57:40,633
I thought there were rules.

590
00:57:40,657 --> 00:57:43,870
I know. This year's different.

591
00:57:43,894 --> 00:57:46,506
Besides, you've been stressed.
You should relax.

592
00:57:46,530 --> 00:57:49,242
Are you sure there's
nothing wrong?

593
00:57:49,266 --> 00:57:51,277
I'd just rather you
stayed in tonight.

594
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:52,979
Peter?

595
00:57:53,003 --> 00:57:56,148
Anyway, I have to put on
my Halloween costume.

596
00:57:56,172 --> 00:57:58,851
Okay. Do I finally
get to see it?

597
00:57:58,875 --> 00:58:00,876
Yes.

598
00:58:36,580 --> 00:58:37,913
Mom?

599
00:58:39,115 --> 00:58:42,584
Mom, do we have any flashlights?

600
00:58:45,789 --> 00:58:47,289
Mom?

601
00:59:12,115 --> 00:59:14,226
Whoa, nice costume.

602
00:59:14,250 --> 00:59:15,861
She's gone.

603
00:59:15,885 --> 00:59:20,289
- What?
- It took my mom. She's gone.

604
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:27,663
Come on. We have to save her.

605
00:59:40,276 --> 00:59:43,255
Well, guys...

606
00:59:43,279 --> 00:59:45,024
Here we go.

607
00:59:45,048 --> 00:59:48,260
Nice costume, Pete, though
I could have guessed.

608
00:59:48,284 --> 00:59:49,829
I almost brought pillowcases,

609
00:59:49,853 --> 00:59:52,398
but I guess we don't
need 'em now.

610
00:59:52,422 --> 00:59:55,624
No.

611
00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:00,339
Are you sure about this?

612
01:00:00,363 --> 01:00:02,975
It took my mom.

613
01:00:02,999 --> 01:00:04,677
I bet if you went to your house,

614
01:00:04,701 --> 01:00:07,002
your parents would be gone, too.

615
01:00:09,773 --> 01:00:11,083
Okay.

616
01:00:11,107 --> 01:00:14,420
Hey, I thought you
were going as a cat.

617
01:00:14,444 --> 01:00:18,024
It annoyed my neighbors.

618
01:00:18,048 --> 01:00:19,892
Skeletons are good, too.

619
01:00:19,916 --> 01:00:21,961
Cat was better.

620
01:00:21,985 --> 01:00:23,295
Hey, where's your costume?

621
01:00:23,319 --> 01:00:26,365
Oh, believe me,
she's wearing it.

622
01:00:26,389 --> 01:00:29,291
- Huh?
- Well, guys.

623
01:00:36,332 --> 01:00:39,178
That's my pumpkin.

624
01:00:39,202 --> 01:00:42,448
Did you carve it like that?

625
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:45,718
No. It disappeared a while ago.

626
01:00:45,742 --> 01:00:48,243
I told you it'd be mad.

627
01:01:16,840 --> 01:01:17,840
Run!

628
01:01:41,498 --> 01:01:42,698
Look.

629
01:01:47,437 --> 01:01:50,372
I wonder if there's
anybody left at all.

630
01:02:15,465 --> 01:02:18,399
I don't those kids are
from our neighborhood.

631
01:02:31,181 --> 01:02:32,947
- I think we should go.
- Yeah.

632
01:02:43,026 --> 01:02:44,526
Go!

633
01:02:48,364 --> 01:02:51,800
Don't look behind you!

634
01:03:04,047 --> 01:03:08,016
I said don't look!

635
01:04:09,000 --> 01:04:14,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

636
01:04:29,465 --> 01:04:31,399
Come on!

637
01:04:42,312 --> 01:04:44,056
Thanks.

638
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:46,525
Now I see why you like
Halloween so much.

639
01:04:46,549 --> 01:04:51,063
- This is great.
- It's not normally like this.

640
01:04:51,087 --> 01:04:52,520
Come on, guys. We gotta go.

641
01:04:59,462 --> 01:05:01,162
This way!

642
01:05:21,651 --> 01:05:23,952
- I think we lost them.
- Not for long.

643
01:05:43,339 --> 01:05:45,340
Where's bill?

644
01:05:50,046 --> 01:05:52,024
What are you doing?

645
01:05:52,048 --> 01:05:54,093
- Go, Peter.
- Come on.

646
01:05:54,117 --> 01:05:56,462
- No.
- What?

647
01:05:56,486 --> 01:05:58,697
Get to those trees. Go, hide.

648
01:05:58,721 --> 01:06:01,200
- Bill!
- You and Maggie gotta stop this.

649
01:06:01,224 --> 01:06:03,235
If you can't, no one can.

650
01:06:03,259 --> 01:06:06,372
Someone's gonna have to stop these
things from being on your tail.

651
01:06:06,396 --> 01:06:08,630
Those things will kill you.

652
01:06:10,366 --> 01:06:14,435
- I run fast.
- No, you don't.

653
01:06:16,372 --> 01:06:19,574
Just go. Get to those trees.
Hide, doofus.

654
01:06:29,552 --> 01:06:33,054
Here goes nothing.

655
01:06:47,403 --> 01:06:50,616
Hey, creepy kid demon!
Over here.

656
01:06:50,640 --> 01:06:54,820
You make me want to throw up...
On your face.

657
01:06:54,844 --> 01:06:57,479
That was a good one.

658
01:07:02,185 --> 01:07:04,185
Gentlemen...

659
01:07:07,390 --> 01:07:08,790
Start your engines.

660
01:07:36,185 --> 01:07:38,630
What is all this?

661
01:07:38,654 --> 01:07:40,655
I don't know.

662
01:07:46,462 --> 01:07:49,641
These are bill's dad's glasses.

663
01:07:49,665 --> 01:07:51,844
He borrowed them once.

664
01:07:51,868 --> 01:07:54,335
They made everything look funny.

665
01:07:57,640 --> 01:08:00,642
And those are his mom's shoes.

666
01:08:10,453 --> 01:08:12,454
That's my mom's.

667
01:08:15,191 --> 01:08:17,258
We have to figure something out.

668
01:08:20,530 --> 01:08:23,742
I don't know.

669
01:08:23,766 --> 01:08:28,480
Okay, so why does
it even want us?

670
01:08:28,504 --> 01:08:30,182
'Cause we scare easily.

671
01:08:30,206 --> 01:08:33,152
- What?
- Think about it.

672
01:08:33,176 --> 01:08:35,854
All this is meant to scare us.

673
01:08:35,878 --> 01:08:38,590
No one believes like kids.

674
01:08:38,614 --> 01:08:40,893
I wish your sister told
us how to kill it.

675
01:08:40,917 --> 01:08:43,351
She didn't know it was real.

676
01:09:10,913 --> 01:09:11,913
Peter!

677
01:09:33,970 --> 01:09:35,737
I know this place.

678
01:09:37,473 --> 01:09:39,318
This is where I was in my dream.

679
01:09:39,342 --> 01:09:41,753
I know this, too. This is it.

680
01:09:41,777 --> 01:09:44,579
This is where it lives.

681
01:09:47,583 --> 01:09:48,816
Stay together.

682
01:10:17,747 --> 01:10:18,747
Peter?

683
01:10:19,882 --> 01:10:20,882
Peter?

684
01:10:24,287 --> 01:10:25,587
Peter?

685
01:11:32,555 --> 01:11:34,689
You can't hurt the
people I love anymore!

686
01:12:38,621 --> 01:12:40,688
I... I lost you.

687
01:12:44,660 --> 01:12:45,660
Maggie?

688
01:12:51,934 --> 01:12:53,835
What's going on? Come on.

689
01:12:55,638 --> 01:12:59,751
It looks like in my dream.
Exactly like.

690
01:12:59,775 --> 01:13:01,787
It's meant to scare us.

691
01:13:01,811 --> 01:13:05,690
What are you talking about?

692
01:13:05,714 --> 01:13:08,449
- There is no monster.
- What?

693
01:13:09,752 --> 01:13:13,432
- Stay away, Peter.
- What are you doing?

694
01:13:13,456 --> 01:13:15,901
It's me. It's coming from me.

695
01:13:15,925 --> 01:13:18,170
Maggie, what?

696
01:13:18,194 --> 01:13:21,006
It's from my bad dreams.
They're coming true.

697
01:13:21,030 --> 01:13:23,508
You're not making sense.

698
01:13:23,532 --> 01:13:28,547
Think about it. Bill said it
started when his mom was little.

699
01:13:28,571 --> 01:13:31,116
When I was little.

700
01:13:31,140 --> 01:13:32,784
It started when I died.

701
01:13:32,808 --> 01:13:34,119
Bill doesn't know anything.

702
01:13:34,143 --> 01:13:38,089
Maybe when something
bad enough happens,

703
01:13:38,113 --> 01:13:39,991
it can change things.

704
01:13:40,015 --> 01:13:41,927
Stop it. You're not doing this.

705
01:13:41,951 --> 01:13:46,587
Believing is seeing. I
think it's real, so it is.

706
01:13:48,224 --> 01:13:51,025
Just stay away from me
before you get hurt, too.

707
01:13:57,533 --> 01:13:58,900
Watch out!

708
01:14:14,149 --> 01:14:16,595
I was wrong.

709
01:14:16,619 --> 01:14:18,697
You should be scared of me.

710
01:14:18,721 --> 01:14:22,033
No, you're just a kid.
It can't be from you.

711
01:14:22,057 --> 01:14:23,502
I mean, how?

712
01:14:23,526 --> 01:14:26,271
I don't know, but it's true.

713
01:14:26,295 --> 01:14:29,040
Besides, it doesn't
look like a monster.

714
01:14:29,064 --> 01:14:33,979
It looks like kids, like,
trick-or-treating.

715
01:14:34,003 --> 01:14:37,749
It's a monster. It has to be.

716
01:14:37,773 --> 01:14:40,151
I'm not afraid of
trick-or-treaters.

717
01:14:40,175 --> 01:14:43,688
No, but I am.

718
01:14:43,712 --> 01:14:47,859
Last Halloween, I was chased
by older kids in masks.

719
01:14:47,883 --> 01:14:50,028
They scared me really bad,

720
01:14:50,052 --> 01:14:53,698
and bill was always scared
of toys coming to life.

721
01:14:53,722 --> 01:14:57,068
I'm not scared of that, either.

722
01:14:57,092 --> 01:14:59,604
- That's it.
- What's it?

723
01:14:59,628 --> 01:15:02,774
- It's all of us.
- What?

724
01:15:02,798 --> 01:15:04,643
It must have started with you,

725
01:15:04,667 --> 01:15:06,678
but now it's spreading
to all of us.

726
01:15:06,702 --> 01:15:11,049
Spreading? What do
you mean, spreading?

727
01:15:11,073 --> 01:15:12,918
Like a germ or something.

728
01:15:12,942 --> 01:15:17,088
Maggie, believing is seeing.
You said it.

729
01:15:17,112 --> 01:15:19,791
No one believes like kids,

730
01:15:19,815 --> 01:15:22,160
so no one gets scared like them.

731
01:15:22,184 --> 01:15:24,796
Don't you see? It's not you.

732
01:15:24,820 --> 01:15:27,165
It's the fear.

733
01:15:27,189 --> 01:15:30,057
It's alive.

734
01:15:31,794 --> 01:15:33,728
We're all feeding it.

735
01:15:36,932 --> 01:15:38,977
We've still gotta stop it.

736
01:15:39,001 --> 01:15:41,780
I don't know how.

737
01:15:41,804 --> 01:15:45,350
It's taking over the whole town.

738
01:15:45,374 --> 01:15:49,187
But... it's fear.

739
01:15:49,211 --> 01:15:51,279
How do you stop that?

740
01:15:56,118 --> 01:15:58,953
What scares you most?

741
01:16:03,759 --> 01:16:05,593
Come on.

742
01:16:10,366 --> 01:16:13,645
That's why all the grown-ups
are disappearing, isn't it?

743
01:16:13,669 --> 01:16:15,570
You're scared of that, too.

744
01:16:23,846 --> 01:16:25,112
I don't like this.

745
01:16:28,984 --> 01:16:32,687
- Ready?
- Okay.

746
01:16:34,890 --> 01:16:35,890
Go!

747
01:17:08,724 --> 01:17:10,725
We've got to cross.

748
01:17:12,061 --> 01:17:14,695
I don't think I can.

749
01:17:28,477 --> 01:17:31,212
- Don't let go.
- I won't.

750
01:18:44,987 --> 01:18:46,898
I remember...

751
01:18:46,922 --> 01:18:49,868
I was mad at my mom, because
she wouldn't let me stay over

752
01:18:49,892 --> 01:18:55,029
at a friend's house, so I
snuck out and got lost.

753
01:19:06,842 --> 01:19:08,987
I think we won.

754
01:19:09,011 --> 01:19:11,156
I forgot it could be pretty.

755
01:19:11,180 --> 01:19:14,259
It's a great spot.

756
01:19:14,283 --> 01:19:16,427
